snippet.textDisplay: I’ve Sjögren’s syndroom, a systemic autoimmune disease that affects my entire body. For years I’ve managed my symptoms with Plaquenil (hydroxychloroquine). A couple of months I stopped taking Plaquenil, because I wanted to know if I could manage Sjogren’s without medication. For a while everything was fine, except of a few mild symptoms such as dry eyes & nose which are common among Sjögren’s patients. But a few weeks ago my Sjögren’s came back with a vengeance. I started to experience joint pain, sore throat, dry mouth & debilitating fatigue. On top of that a few days ago I developed a heavy dry cough & this horrible headache and neck pain which I have never experienced before. My heart was also racing and I had trouble catching my breath. I was afraid that I had the coronavirus because people with Sjögren’s are predisposed to infections. so I called my GP, she didn’t want to test me for the coronavirus because I didn’t have a fever. Besides they didn’t have enough tests. A few hours later my symptoms got worse: my body felt like it was on fire. I felt this tight pressure around my heart, specially every time I coughed. I felt like I was suffocating. I knew something was wrong, because I have never experienced these symptoms before. Deep down I knew I had the virus; I had all the symptoms except for fever, but I noticed my body temperature was going up. I remembered reading an article online about a study conducted by Wuhan doctors that showed a few patients were cured from the virus by taking Hydroxychloroquine. Their symptoms improved 80% after taking 600mg of Hydroxychloroquine. I had one box of Hydroxychloroquine left, so I decided to take it again. After a few hours I noticed a change in my symptoms. I coughed less & my lungs hurt less. The next day my sore throat, headache & tightness around my chest were gone completely. I felt like a complete different person. For the first time in weeks I had the energy to do some chores in the house. I wasn’t out of breath anymore. I truly believe that Hydroxychloroquine saved my life by suppressing the symptoms of the coronavirus. I know I can’t prove I had the coronavirus, because I wasn’t tested. But based on my symptoms, I believe that I had the virus. I haven’t fully recovered yet. I still feel very weak, I'm at home resting now. I live between my bed and the couch. My body still doesn’t feel the same, I feel exhausted by just walking to my bed.
